Kyle Seitz received two years of conditional release after pleading guilty to criminally negligent homicide in the death of his 15-month-old son Benjamin . 
  Seitz forgot to take his son to day care on July 7 and left him in the car for seven hours while he went to work . 
  His wife Lindsey Rogers-Seitz wrote a letter in court asking the judge for leniency . 
  Judge Kevin Russo spared Seitz from prison time and said he had suffered enough . 
  Benjamin died of hyperthermia after being left in the hot car . 
 